23/10/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A district court judge ordered on Thursday (October 22nd) that seven former Croatian soldiers be detained for a month. 
All are suspected of committing war crimes against five Serbian soldiers in 1995. 
The crimes allegedly occurred on Bosnian territory at the end of the country's 1992-1995 conflict. 
The seven were arrested on Tuesday. 
(Nacional, HINA, RTS, AP - 22/10/09)
